                                 Suidas relates him contemporary with Ninus King of Assyria;
Eusebius, with Semiramis Wife of Ninus; Ninus is placed by Chronologers
above the 3447. of the Julian Period.

To these adde, cited by the Arabians, a Treatise of Magick; and
another, of Dreams and their Interpretation, cited by Gelaldin frequently;
Inventions doubtlesse of latter times.

The Amilicti [implacable] are Powers so termed,Psell. in Orac. for that they
are firm and not to be converted towards these inferiour things;
and also cause that Souls be not allured by affections.

